00:00:01:200000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:01:200000.Dialogue: You know who's got to be the bravest person in the Marvel Universe? Whoever has to give She-Hulk a bikini wax.

00:00:08:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:08:180000.Dialogue: You want to talk brave, how about Captain America's undocumented Mexican gardener?

00:00:14:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:14:210000.Dialogue: He's not braver than whoever uses the bathroom after the thing?

00:00:19:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:19:110000.Dialogue: As usual, you're all wrong. The bravest person in the Marvel Universe is the doctor who gives wolverine his prostate exam.

00:00:28:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:28:020000.Dialogue: How about the guy who gets a prostate exam from wolverine?

00:00:34:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:34:040000.Dialogue: Wolverine's never displayed the slightest interest in helping others prevent prostate cancer.

00:00:42:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:42:200000.Dialogue: Hello. Yes, the elevator's out of order£¬ you'll have to use the stairs. Of course you can. Pizza dates back to the 16th century, while the first elevator was not installed until 1852. That means that for over 300 years, people carried pizzas up stairs.

00:01:00:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:00:130000.Dialogue: Be part of that proud tradition.

00:01:04:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:04:100000.Dialogue: I'll go get Penny while that guy spits on our food.

00:01:09:150000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:09:150000.Dialogue: Do you think they gave wolverine an Adamantium prostate?

00:01:14:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:01:14:230000.Dialogue: We're having a conversation about probing the heinies of superheroes. There are no stupid questions.

00:01:36:060000.Speaker: Man
00:01:36:060000.Dialogue: Damn, it's good to finally meet you, son.

00:01:39:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:39:000000.Dialogue: Okay, I think a bit of context here might help.

00:01:42:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:42:020000.Dialogue: Oh, hey, Leonard. I see you met my dad.

00:01:46:200000.Speaker: Penny’s Dad
00:01:46:200000.Dialogue: Come on in, buddy. Take a load off.

00:01:48:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:48:170000.Dialogue: Oh, gee, dad, Leonard can't stay. He just dropped by to say hello. Thanks for stopping by, sweetie. I'll see you later.

00:02:30:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:30:200000.Dialogue: Are you sure you have enough comics? You're going to be monitoring the telescope for 12 hours, and by my estimate, you've only selected seven hours of reading material.

00:02:40:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:40:110000.Dialogue: That's even factoring in your difficulty in parsing American comic book idioms like "Bamf!" and "Snikt!"

00:02:47:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:47:120000.Dialogue: Is that racist? It feels racist.

00:02:51:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:51:030000.Dialogue: Don't be oversensitive. He's calling you illiterate, not your race.

00:02:59:000000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:59:000000.Dialogue: I don't need more comics. Howard's gonna stop by, we're gonna play intergalactic battleship and Indian Monopoly.

00:03:04:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:04:110000.Dialogue: I don't care for novelty editions of Monopoly. I prefer the classics regular and Klingon.

00:03:11:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:11:230000.Dialogue: Actually, Indian Monopoly's just like regular, except the money's in Rupees, instead of hotels you build call centers,

00:03:18:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:18:150000.Dialogue: and when you pick a chance card, you might die of dysentery.

00:03:28:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:28:220000.Dialogue: You'll never guess what just happened.

00:03:30:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:30:200000.Dialogue: You went out in the hallway, Stumbled into an interdimensional portal which brought you 5,000 years into the future, where you took advantage of the advanced technology to build a time machine, and now you're back to bring us all with you to the year 7010 where we are transported to work at the thinkatorium by telepathically controlled flying dolphins?

00:03:56:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:56:060000.Dialogue: Well, who would ever guess that?

00:03:59:040000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:59:040000.Dialogue: What... what kind of a kiss?

00:04:00:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:00:170000.Dialogue: A big kiss. On the mouth.

00:04:02:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:02:180000.Dialogue: Is it possible that she was going for your cheek and you moved and she accidentally got lip? That happens with me and my mom all the time.

00:04:11:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:11:210000.Dialogue: She introduced me to her father, kissed me and then shut the door in my face.

00:04:16:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:16:230000.Dialogue: Maybe she was trying to send you a message.

00:04:19:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:19:200000.Dialogue: Yeah. "This man is not my father. I'm being held hostage. So I'm going to do something insane in the hopes that you'll call 911."

00:04:27:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:27:140000.Dialogue: Penny kissing me is not insane. She used to kiss me all the time.

00:04:31:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:31:010000.Dialogue: Einstein defined insanity as "doing the same thing over and over again and expecting different results. " By that standard, Penny is cuckoo for cocoa puffs.

00:04:42:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:42:160000.Dialogue: I'm just saying, it felt like it may have meant something.

00:04:46:000000.Speaker: Howard
00:04:46:000000.Dialogue: Ah, this takes me back. Leonard obsessing about Penny. I mean, don't get me wrong, I love your new stuff, but once in a while it's nice to hear the hits.

00:04:55:000000.Speaker: Raj
00:04:55:000000.Dialogue: Ooh, ooh! Do "Our babies will be smart and beautiful. "

00:05:01:010000.Speaker: Raj
00:05:01:010000.Dialogue: That one always makes me laugh.

00:05:05:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:05:140000.Dialogue: Why do I bother talking to you people?

00:05:07:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:07:160000.Dialogue: If it'll make you feel better, we rarely listen.

00:05:11:010000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:11:010000.Dialogue: Hey, can I talk to you out here for a sec?

00:05:15:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:15:060000.Dialogue: I'm starting to think we're never going to see that pizza.

00:05:19:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:19:190000.Dialogue: So you're probably wondering what that was all about.

00:05:22:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:22:020000.Dialogue: What, uh, the kissing and everything? Nah, women do that to me all the time.

00:05:27:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:27:220000.Dialogue: Yeah, okay. The thing is, I kind of told my father we got back together again.

00:05:32:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:32:220000.Dialogue: Well, you're the first guy he's ever really approved of, you know? You're a scientist who went to college and you don't have a neck tattoo or outstanding warrants or... or a baby.

00:05:44:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:44:130000.Dialogue: What kind of guys did you used to go out with?

00:05:47:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:47:230000.Dialogue: Just guys. Anyway, when I told him we split up, he was heartbroken, and he kept bugging me: "How's Leonard? why can't you get back together with Leonard? I bet Leonard never tipped a cow over on himself. "

00:05:59:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:59:070000.Dialogue: So to get him off my back, I told him we worked things out.

00:06:11:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:11:130000.Dialogue: I mean, did you apologize? Did you have to woo me?

00:06:17:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:17:100000.Dialogue: Get over yourself. I whistled, you came running.

00:06:21:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:21:220000.Dialogue: Yeah, no, I don't think so.

00:06:23:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:23:100000.Dialogue: Okay, why are you arguing about this?

00:06:25:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:25:140000.Dialogue: I'm just saying, if we fake got back together, that's totally not how it fake happened.

00:06:29:010000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:29:010000.Dialogue: Oh... Okay, whatever. Will you please just play along until my dad leaves?

00:06:33:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:33:020000.Dialogue: Hold on, you actually want me to deceive your father with some sort of sham playacting and kissing? Cause I'm good with that.

00:06:49:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:49:190000.Dialogue: Come on, honey, not in front of my dad.

00:06:52:010000.Speaker: Penny's Dad
00:06:52:010000.Dialogue: Relax, I've seen you do a lot worse with a lot stupider.

00:06:58:210000.Speaker: Penny’s Dad
00:06:58:210000.Dialogue: So, Leonard, I'm taking your gal out for a steak dinner, you want to join us?

00:07:01:150000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:01:150000.Dialogue: Oh, dad, that's nice, but Leonard has to work. Right, Leonard?

00:07:04:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:04:180000.Dialogue: Uh, I do, I have to work. But I'm gonna blow that off to spend the evening with my sweetie and her father, 'cause, you know, just the kind of boyfriend I am.

00:07:26:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:26:110000.Dialogue: How could that be a miss? C-6 was a hit, c-8 was a hit. Part of your starship has to be on c-7.

00:07:32:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:07:32:110000.Dialogue: Not if it has a hole in the middle.

00:07:35:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:35:200000.Dialogue: What kind of spaceship has a hole in the middle?

00:07:46:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:46:150000.Dialogue: Oh, great, you made it. Come on in. I invited her.

00:07:53:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:53:030000.Dialogue: It's in hawaii, but Raj controls it from here. He's hoping to see epsilon eridani dim, which would be evidence of a planet orbiting it.

00:08:01:040000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:08:01:040000.Dialogue: So we just sit and stare at the screen, waiting for something to happen?

00:08:05:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:05:050000.Dialogue: I did it with you when we rented "The Notebook".

00:08:12:000000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:12:000000.Dialogue: Yes, Gena Rowlands is a treasure.

00:08:16:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:16:040000.Dialogue: You'd better open up that bottle of wine or I'm gonna end up with swimmer's ear.

00:08:21:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:21:120000.Dialogue: Excuse me. I can't be drinking, I'm about to make an important scientific discovery here.

00:08:26:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:26:030000.Dialogue: What? Galileo did his best work while drinking wine.

00:08:30:140000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:30:140000.Dialogue: Well, he was Italian. It's a reasonable assumption.

00:08:34:140000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:34:140000.Dialogue: Dude, can you even open your mouth without spewing a cultural stereotype?

00:08:38:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:38:020000.Dialogue: Oh, I... I'm sorry, Galileo drank diet sprite.

00:08:42:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:42:020000.Dialogue: Look, you're my best friend, she's my girlfriend, you should bond. You know, like you and my mom did.

00:08:47:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:47:170000.Dialogue: Your mom creeps the hell out of me.

00:08:50:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:50:200000.Dialogue: Yes, but she's stopped calling you slumdog millionaire.

00:08:59:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:59:050000.Dialogue: I'd like to propose a toast. To science and friendship.

00:09:05:160000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:09:05:160000.Dialogue: Hold on. Wait. No, it's okay, go ahead.

00:09:09:220000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:09:09:220000.Dialogue: Oh, I was working with Penicillin-resistant gonorrhea in the lab today and I was just trying to remember if I washed my hands.

00:09:24:130000.Speaker: Penny's Dad
00:09:24:130000.Dialogue: My pleasure. It's nice to have dinner with a boyfriend of Penny's that knows how to use a napkin.

00:09:32:120000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:09:32:120000.Dialogue: Let me tell you about this one genius she was going out with, This... this fella Donnie.

00:09:36:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:36:020000.Dialogue: Oh, will you please let it go?

00:09:37:100000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:09:37:100000.Dialogue: Donnie was gonna make millions turning farm waste into biofuel and selling it to the government.

00:09:42:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:42:040000.Dialogue: A lot of people are doing that.

00:09:44:060000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:09:44:060000.Dialogue: Yeah, but all Donnie did was mix pig poop with a little water and pump it into his mom's Camry.

00:09:50:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:50:200000.Dialogue: Yeah, that's great. It's a funny story. Moving on.

00:09:53:120000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:09:53:120000.Dialogue: And Donnie was a rocket scientist compared to that boy who wanted to get beer pong into the olympics. What was his name, sweetheart?

00:09:59:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:59:020000.Dialogue: Curtis, and I'm pretty sure he was joking.

00:10:01:120000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:10:01:120000.Dialogue: I don't know. That petition looked real to me.

00:10:04:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:04:230000.Dialogue: Yeah, okay, I think this ends the ex-boyfriend portion of our evening.

00:10:08:150000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:10:08:150000.Dialogue: Well, I'm just glad you finally found yourself a keeper.

00:10:19:230000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:10:19:230000.Dialogue: Leonard, you want to come in for a nightcap?

00:10:21:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:21:130000.Dialogue: Oh, gee, dad, he'd love to, but Leonard has to work in the morning.

00:10:24:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:24:150000.Dialogue: Maybe I could go in a little late.

00:10:26:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:26:120000.Dialogue: No, no, no, you can't. Your career is far too important.

00:10:29:220000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:10:29:220000.Dialogue: Behind every great man is a nagging woman who won't let him have any fun, am I right, Leonard?

00:10:40:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:40:020000.Dialogue: Good night, Wyatt. Oh, good night, honey.

00:11:06:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:06:220000.Dialogue: Three, four, five... pass go, get 2,000 Rupees... Six, seven. Whoops. Can't go any further. There's a sacred cow in my way.

00:11:17:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:17:110000.Dialogue: Bernadette, please tell your boyfriend to cool it with the cow jokes.

00:11:20:030000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:11:20:030000.Dialogue: It won't help. Once he finds a joke he likes, he sticks with it.

00:11:26:010000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:11:26:010000.Dialogue: Oh, right. Did you get your hair cut?

00:11:27:230000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:27:230000.Dialogue: No. I got them all cut.

00:11:34:150000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:34:150000.Dialogue: And when you go to a Chinese restaurant, he always gets the same fortune in his fortune cookie.

00:11:38:180000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:11:38:180000.Dialogue: Right. "Help, I'm a prisoner in a Chinese fortune cookie factory. "

00:11:44:010000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:44:010000.Dialogue: Okay, I think that's enough about me.

00:11:46:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:46:120000.Dialogue: He's right. Let's make fun of his mother.

00:11:49:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:11:49:160000.Dialogue: Howard, come rub my feet!                   My corns are killing me!

00:11:55:180000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:11:55:180000.Dialogue: Howard, help me out of the tub!                I'm stuck again!

00:12:13:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:13:090000.Dialogue: You know what I've been doing for the last hour?

00:12:15:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:15:050000.Dialogue: Mm, dreamily doodling "Mrs. Leonard Hofstadter" in a notebook?

00:12:19:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:19:200000.Dialogue: Listening to my father go on and on about what a great guy you are.

00:12:23:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:23:060000.Dialogue: You got to admit, I am... I'm delightful.

00:12:27:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:27:120000.Dialogue: Why are you making this so difficult?

00:12:29:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:29:060000.Dialogue: It's not difficult for me. I'm having fun.

00:12:33:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:33:170000.Dialogue: What do you want me to do? You started this. Do you want to go over and tell him we're broken up?

00:12:39:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:39:120000.Dialogue: Don't you think that's something you should have figured out before you stomped over here?

00:12:45:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:45:140000.Dialogue: Leonard, Penny, excellent. I'd like to say I'm very happy that you're back together, and if I can figure out a way to do so and sound sincere, I will.

00:12:55:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:55:050000.Dialogue: In the meantime, I'd like to go over some proposed changes to the roommate agreement specifically to address Penny's annoying personal habits.

00:13:03:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:03:040000.Dialogue: Oh, my God. What personal habits?

00:13:07:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:07:120000.Dialogue: FYI, overuse of the phrase "oh, my god" is number 12.

00:13:12:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:12:080000.Dialogue: Okay, Sheldon, you don't have to do this because Leonard and I are not... - Ba-ba-ba-ba. Are you sure you want to include him in this?

00:13:17:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:17:140000.Dialogue: Include me in what? Is there a plot afoot? I'll have no truck with plots.

00:13:23:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:23:130000.Dialogue: No, you're right. No, there's... There's no plots, no trucks, no feet.

00:13:28:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:28:070000.Dialogue: So what other annoying habits shall we discuss?

00:13:30:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:30:180000.Dialogue: Uh, we don't discuss anything. Leonard is the signatory to the Roommate Agreement. As such, he bears responsibility for all your infractions and must pay all fines.

00:13:41:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:41:100000.Dialogue: Fines? - Yes. If Penny's going to be spending nights here again,

00:13:44:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:44:020000.Dialogue: you'll need to set up an escrow account. Sign here.

00:13:51:110000.Speaker: Raj
00:13:51:110000.Dialogue: Hello, Hawaii. This is Dr. Koothrappali in Pasadena. I'd like you to reposition the telescope, please. Scarlett Johansson's house!

00:14:09:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:09:130000.Dialogue: It might have been a mistake to open that second bottle of wine.

00:14:13:040000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:14:13:040000.Dialogue: Well, live and learn. So, Raj, do you think this planet you're looking for could have an atmosphere that supports life?

00:14:20:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:20:050000.Dialogue: Maybe. If it did, I'd be famous. I'd be on the cover of magazines. And then, instead of living alone in my tiny apartment, I'd have a big mansion.

00:14:30:120000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:30:120000.Dialogue: It is. If you like wandering around a big, empty house with no one to love you.

00:14:44:130000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:44:130000.Dialogue: My only friends would be my genetically engineered monkey butler. And the little people I hired to be my living chess set.

00:14:53:120000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:14:53:120000.Dialogue: He's taking a turn to the dark side, isn't he?

00:14:55:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:55:210000.Dialogue: Hold on. He could come back.

00:14:57:130000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:57:130000.Dialogue: Oh, what's the point of everything?

00:15:01:080000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:01:080000.Dialogue: You know it's been more than a year since i've even kissed a girl?

00:15:04:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:04:150000.Dialogue: What about that hookup at Comic-Con you told me about?

00:15:07:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:15:07:050000.Dialogue: Oh, grow up. I was lying. I lie all the time. Nobody wants to kiss me.

00:15:11:200000.Speaker: Bernadette
00:15:11:200000.Dialogue: Oh, you poor, poor thing. Raj, you have to know you're a wonderful man. There are a lot of girls out there who'll want to kiss you.

00:15:45:230000.Scene: The apartment. Wyatt and Leonard are playing Wii fishing.
00:15:45:230000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:15:45:230000.Dialogue: Oh! I think I got a nibble.

00:15:47:220000.Scene: The apartment. Wyatt and Leonard are playing Wii fishing.
00:15:47:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:47:220000.Dialogue: Oh, be careful. Give him some line. Okay, now reel him in.

00:15:55:060000.Scene: The apartment. Wyatt and Leonard are playing Wii fishing.
00:15:55:060000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:15:55:060000.Dialogue: Oh, look at that baby. They're really biting, huh?

00:15:58:020000.Scene: The apartment. Wyatt and Leonard are playing Wii fishing.
00:15:58:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:15:58:020000.Dialogue: Yeah. They do that when you set it on easy.

00:16:03:020000.Scene: The apartment. Wyatt and Leonard are playing Wii fishing.
00:16:03:020000.Speaker: Wyatt

00:16:06:000000.Scene: The apartment. Wyatt and Leonard are playing Wii fishing.
00:16:06:000000.Speaker: wyatt
00:16:06:000000.Dialogue: Hello. Oh, hi, sweetie. Yeah, I got up early and didn't want to wake you, so I went out for coffee and ran into Leonard on the way back. Guess what... We're fishing. Yeah. Right here on his couch.

00:16:19:150000.Scene: The apartment. Wyatt and Leonard are playing Wii fishing.
00:16:19:150000.Speaker: Leonard

00:16:24:000000.Scene: The apartment. Wyatt and Leonard are playing Wii fishing.
00:16:24:000000.Speaker: wyatt
00:16:24:000000.Dialogue: That's Leonard says he loves you. What?

00:16:31:080000.Scene: The apartment. Wyatt and Leonard are playing Wii fishing.
00:16:31:080000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:16:31:080000.Dialogue: I see. The whole thing's bull squirt, huh? Well, that's very disappointing. Bye.

00:16:47:230000.Scene: The apartment. Wyatt and Leonard are playing Wii fishing.
00:16:47:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:47:230000.Dialogue: Oh, hey. There's been something I've been meaning to tell you.

00:16:53:040000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:16:53:040000.Dialogue: I can't believe you would lie to me like that.

00:16:55:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:55:040000.Dialogue: Just for the record, I did not want to be a part of this.

00:16:56:210000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:16:56:210000.Dialogue: I'll get to you in a minute.

00:17:00:030000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:17:00:030000.Dialogue: That my own daughter thinks I don't love her enough To support her no matter what choices she makes... Well, that hurts me deeply.

00:17:07:130000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:17:07:130000.Dialogue: I thought we were past the days when you would try to pull the wool over my eyes. Telling me the baggie in your underwear drawer is potpourri?

00:17:15:190000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:17:15:190000.Dialogue: And the pee stick in your bathroom Is to check for diabetes?

00:17:24:220000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:17:24:220000.Dialogue: You're a grown woman, and I respect your right To make your own decisions, but all I ask is you respect me enough to be honest about them.

00:17:31:010000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:31:010000.Dialogue: You're right. Look, from now on, I will tell you the truth.

00:17:33:190000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:17:33:190000.Dialogue: Thank you. Now, why don't you go and put some clothes on and we'll grab a bite to eat before I head for the airport. Now you.

00:17:38:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:38:120000.Dialogue: - Daddy, he had nothing to do...

00:17:46:040000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:17:46:040000.Dialogue: Please, please, please don't give up on her.

00:17:53:010000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:17:53:010000.Dialogue: I can't go back to the skateboard idiots, the white rappers and all those Sweaty dumb-asses with their backwards hats.

00:18:01:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:01:050000.Dialogue: Gee, I don't know if it's in the cards, sir.

00:18:06:030000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:18:06:030000.Dialogue: Cheat. Lie. I don't care. I want grandkids before I die, and I want them to grow up in a house without wheels.

00:18:21:150000.Speaker: Wyatt
00:18:21:150000.Dialogue: Thank you. Now I'm going to do something here to help you along.

00:18:32:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:32:110000.Dialogue: Oh, the reverse psychology thing. I see. That's very clever.

00:18:46:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:46:220000.Dialogue: Oh, there you are. Just so you know, I was up all night, but I have finally completed The Penny-specific section of the new roommate agreement.

00:18:57:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:57:120000.Dialogue: Yeah, well, not necessary. We broke up again.

00:19:12:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:12:230000.Dialogue: Do you even think about other people, leonard?

00:19:27:130000.Speaker: Raj
00:19:27:130000.Dialogue: Oh, you know. Same old, same old. Looked through a telescope, saw some stars. Big whoop.

00:19:35:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:19:35:070000.Dialogue: Really? You waited months for time with that telescope. What happened?

00:19:41:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:41:190000.Dialogue: I'm going to propose a hypothesis. Last night, Raj accidentally made contact With an alien civilization

00:19:49:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:49:070000.Dialogue: and has been ordered by the United States government To keep it a secret.

00:19:55:000000.Speaker: Raj
00:19:55:000000.Dialogue: Nothing happened. Can we please just change the subject?

00:19:57:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:19:57:130000.Dialogue: That sounds rehearsed. We are not alone.

00:20:07:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:20:07:120000.Dialogue: You get to play with raj's big telescope last night?

00:20:12:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:20:12:100000.Dialogue: Whoa. Where did that come from?

00:20:19:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:20:19:170000.Dialogue: I did shut up. Now you shut up.
